Paniai has always been a problem for the Indonesian government.
The lack of real development feeds discontent in the Mee, Moni, Dani, and Damal tribes living in the lush central highlands of Papua.
Many have joined the Papua Liberation Movement (OPM), an army of rebels that claims to defend the rights of the Papuans with random attacks and kidnappings of Indonesian army soldiers.
Some of the leaders of the OPM are Paniai, such as Tadius Yogi and Daniel Yudas Kogoya.
The army has responded to the rebellion by arbitrarily arresting and imprisoning thousands of people in Paniai in the name of "protecting national sovereignty".
