"It wasn't the kind of murder we're already used to and could be called typical.
That's when I felt the chills.
I was angry and crying.”
He booked a return flight home for the next day.
The plane landed at 11 p.m. Ferrell picked up his six-year-old daughter from her father's house and decided that they would go to Ferguson the next morning.
What Happened to Ferrell and Ferguson in the Next Nearly Three Years has been made into a documentary film "Whose Streets?". It premiered in cinemas on August 11, 2017.
