"One of our questions was whether this was a violation of the Hatch Act. We were told not to," the commander wrote.
"It sounds like you can participate," the assistant commandant replied.
Made in America was an official White House event, so it was not covered by the Hatch Act.
But even official events have political tones.
At the event, the president spoke out in favour of the health care reform that was being discussed by the Senate at the time, as well as looser state regulation.
The use of the Marine One helicopter and the Air Force One aircraft for political purposes is not a new phenomenon.
Presidents must use them on their journeys,
